# Onyx container (theme kit)

When the user asks to **apply onyx container** / **utiliser onyx container** /
**même shell que plan financier**, use this recipe — do not invent a new card shell.

## Source of truth

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Component | `apps/mobile/components/OnyxContainer.tsx` (alias of `PlanFinanceContainer`) |
| Tokens | `ONYX_CONTAINER`, `onyxContainerShellStyle`, `onyxContainerPressedStyle`, `onyxContainerRowLayoutStyle` in `apps/mobile/constants/planFinanceKit.ts` |
| Halo | `planFinanceCardHalo` (on by default) |

Legacy name `PlanFinanceContainer` / `PLAN_FINANCE_CONTAINER` is the same shell — prefer **Onyx** in new code and when following a user request.

## Shell properties

- Fill: `colors.containerBackground` (`#111111` dark)
- Outline: `colors.containerBorder` + `StyleSheet.hairlineWidth`
- Radius: **13px**
- Halo: charcoal lift (default `halo`)
- Press: wrap `Pressable` + `onyxContainerPressedStyle()` (opacity **0.82**)

## Apply pattern

```tsx
import { OnyxContainer } from '@/components/OnyxContainer';
import { ONYX_CONTAINER, onyxContainerPressedStyle } from '@/constants/planFinanceKit';

<Pressable style={({ pressed }) => [pressed && onyxContainerPressedStyle()]}>
  <OnyxContainer style={{ padding: ONYX_CONTAINER.padding.card, gap: spacing.md }}>
    {children}
  </OnyxContainer>
</Pressable>
```

## Do not use for

- Glass inputs, segmented controls
- Protected `TransactionDetailSheet.tsx` unless explicitly requested
- Places that must keep the older 18px `containerSurfaceStyle` / `SurfaceCard` glass look
